== Value IV: Commonality ==
The Project is defined as the Greatest Common Divisor among
* [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peer-to-peer p2p] [http://p2pfoundation.net/Category:Movements movements]
* [http://hackerspaces.org Hackerspaces]
* [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pirate_Party Pirate parties]
* [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Micronation Micronations]
* "State hack" projects (first steps in this direction: [http://www.freestateproject.org/ Free State Project] and [http://immi.is/ Icelandic Modern Media Initiative])
* [http://theunitedpersons.org/ The United Persons]
specifically, the [[#Members|initiating organizations]] as an informed reference group, within
* the core ideology of the Project:
** [[#Core_Ideology:_Purpose|Purpose]] and
** [[#Core_Ideology:_Values|Values]], and
* the scope of the Project, i.e. [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tax taxation].

Constraint: the predetermination of the desirable scope of the state is certainly not included in the Greatest Common Divisor. The [[#Concept|contestable]] tax market of [[#Definitions|intangibles]] (i.e., the consequence of the desirable scope of the taxation by the state) should shape the environment for the states and they will proactively/reactively adapt themselves to this environment.

